
---

##  Project Objectives

- Build a webpage that conforms to **WCAG 2.1 AA**.
- Use only **custom HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**.
- Evaluate accessibility using:
  - **WAVE automated testing**
  - **Heuristic Evaluation (Nielsen)**
- Conduct improvements based on automated and manual evaluations.
- Document the development over time using **GitHub version control**.

---

##  Features Implemented

###  Accessibility
- Semantic HTML structure (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`).
- Proper heading hierarchy.
- Sufficient text contrast.
- Skip-to-content link.
- Form labels associated with inputs.
- ARIA attributes (`aria-live`, `role="status"`).
- Keyboard-accessible custom elements.
- Accessible tables with `<th scope="col">`.

###  Usability
- Clear organisation and navigation.
- Consistent layout.
- Simple product configuration options.
- Clear error handling on quantity input.

